ce:section.ce:para:
Transmission electron microscopic (TEM) images of QCDs (Fig. 1
                        ) demonstrated well dispersed and spherical for them. HRTEM images of the fluorescent fractions (Fig. 1, inset) revealed clearly that they were monodisperse nanocrystals with a lattice spacing of 0.33 nm (Fig. 2
                        , inset), which is very close to that for the 002 facet of graphite. Therefore, the fluorescent fractions obtained in this work were graphite-structured CNPs. The nano crystals had a uniform spherical shape and a narrow size distribution of 8.0 ± 3.0 nm in diameter. This was further supported by X-ray diffraction (XRD) pattern (Fig. 3
                        ).
